v 3
d svmachines
d Support Vector Machines for both Classification and Regression
d
d Support vector machines (SVM) refers to supervised algorithms 
d for statistical machine learning.  This accommodates both 
d classification and regression as well as the “nu” variant 
d for classification and regression. This package is a thin wrapper 
d for the widely deployed libsvm.
d
d Nick Guenther <nguenthe@uwaterloo.ca> and Matthias Schonlau <schonlau@uwaterloo.ca>
d
d Comment on .pkg file:  WIN64A OS was used in Stata 13 and is supplanted by WIN64 as for Stata14 or 15.
d  For backward compatibility, we list both
d
d Distribution-Date: 20220316

f ../_/_svm_model2stata.ado
f ../_/_svm_train.ado
f ../e/export_svmlight.ado
f ../e/export_svmlight.sthlp
f ../i/import_svmlight.ado
f ../i/import_svmlight.sthlp
f ../s/svm_ensurelib.ado
f ../s/svm_examples.ihlp
f ../s/svm_predict.ado
f ../s/svmachines.ado
f ../s/svmachines.sthlp
f ../s/svmachines_example.ado
f ../s/svmlight.sthlp
G LINUX64 ../_/_svm_dlopenable_LINUX64.plugin _svm_dlopenable.plugin
G LINUX64 ../_/_svm_getenv_LINUX64.plugin _svm_getenv.plugin
G LINUX64 ../_/_svm_setenv_LINUX64.plugin _svm_setenv.plugin
G LINUX64 ../_/_svmachines_LINUX64.plugin _svmachines.plugin
G LINUX64 ../_/_svmlight_LINUX64.plugin _svmlight.plugin
